<seg id=1> Fujian to Boost Cooperation with Taiwan in Economy and Trade </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency. Fuzhou. Jan 10. (Reporter Xuting) Fujian province recently said it will devote great effort to boost cooperation with Taiwan in economy and trade this year. Specfic measures to be taken included: double its effort to attract Taiwan's business, strengthen the ties with Taiwan's big enterprises and big financial groups,introduce a set of large Taiwan-funded items, exert great effort to promote trade with Taiwan and develop cooperation with Taiwan in fishery sevices. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> Recently Fujian province worked out new measures to quicken its development in foreign economic cooperation and trade, among which deepening the reform of internationlly-oriented enterprises, maintaining the steady growth in export as well as continuing to expand foreign investment utilization are ranked as the focuses of Fujian province's foreign economic cooperation and trade in the year of 1998. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Fujian is one of China's coastal regions which witnessed fastest growth in foreign economic cooperation and trade. </seg>
<seg id=5> Last year its total volume of import and export was about US$ 20 billion, the amount of  foreign investment actually used surpassed US$ 4 billion,and the external contract project and service cooperation reached US$ 355 million. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> It was said that the new measures included the following points: stressing  the development of scale management and the establishment of enterprises groups, stimulate strategic reshuffle of province-run internationally-oriented companies; double the effort to promote the export of product from some key industries; successfully conduct foreign investment introduction conference held in Hongkong and 1998 China's investment and trade meeting. </seg>
</p>
